Jaime Zapata is a senior vice president at GMMB, a public affairs marketing firm. He was previously the Deputy Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the U.S. Department of Labor.[1] He was the Reading Clerk of the U.S. House of Representative during the period July 2008  June 2009, and the first ever Hispanic in this position.[2] he has also worked as a spokesman for NABE and the American Federation of Teachers. 
